### Steps to reproduce

Adding a `WidgetSpan` to a `Text.rich` that's in a `SelectionArea` will cause a `SelectionListenerNotifier`'s `selection.range.endOffset` to adjust whenever the text-selection goes over the `WidgetSpans`. This prevents us from being able to compute what the selected text is, based on the offsets of the `selection.range`.

When you remove the `WidgetSpan`, everything works as expected. Placing a `SelectionContainer.disabled()` in the `WidgetSpan` does not fix the issue. Replacing the `FlutterLogo` with a `SizedBox.shrink` does not fix the issue.

### Expected results

A text-selection that includes `WidgetSpan`s should not affect the `endOffset` of a `selection.range`. 

### Actual results

A text-selection that includes `WidgetSpan`s does affect the `endOffset` of a `selection.range`.

### Code sample

<details open><summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'dart:async';

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/rendering.dart';

Future<void> main() async {
  runApp(MaterialApp(home: SelectionApp()));
}

class SelectionApp extends StatefulWidget {
  const SelectionApp({super.key});

  @override
  State<SelectionApp> createState() => _SelectionAppState();
}

class _SelectionAppState extends State<SelectionApp> {
  late SelectionListenerNotifier selectionListenerNotifier;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    selectionListenerNotifier = SelectionListenerNotifier();
    selectionListenerNotifier.addListener(() {
      if (selectionListenerNotifier.selection.status != SelectionStatus.none) {
        print(selectionListenerNotifier.selection.range);
      }
    });
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    super.dispose();
    selectionListenerNotifier.dispose();
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: Padding(
        padding: EdgeInsets.all(32),
        child: SelectionArea(
          child: SelectionListener(
            selectionNotifier: selectionListenerNotifier,
            child: Text.rich(
              style: TextStyle(fontSize: 32),
              TextSpan(
                children: [
                  for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++) ...[
                    WidgetSpan(child: SelectionContainer.disabled(child: FlutterLogo(size: 24))),
                    TextSpan(text: '$i\n'),
                  ],
                ],
              ),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

</details>


