### Use case

I've tried to build a TextField subclass which had OnFocus and OnUnfocus events to easily allow validation as the user leaves one control for another (unfocus). I discovered that the TextField creates a FocusNode, etc. and a listener, (in for _TextFieldState._handleFocusChanged) and it doesn't share it

Please consider adding this as it will not affect the standard component library while making a common user flow (validation on unfocus) easy for developers

### Proposal

One can get the desired behaviour (almost) with some non-scalable code, but perhaps this should live inside a component and not require as much boilerplaate

For two fields:
```
  final usernameKey = GlobalKey<FormFieldState>();
  final passwordKey = GlobalKey<FormFieldState>();
  
late FocusNode usernameFocusNode;
  late FocusNode passwordFocusNode;
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();

    usernameFocusNode = FocusNode();
    passwordFocusNode = FocusNode();

    usernameFocusNode.addListener(usernameFocusIn);
    passwordFocusNode.addListener(passwordFocusIn);
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    usernameFocusNode.dispose();
    passwordFocusNode.dispose();

    super.dispose();
  }

  void usernameFocusIn() {
    usernameFocusNode.removeListener(usernameFocusIn);
    usernameFocusNode.addListener(usernameFocusOut);
  }

  void passwordFocusIn() {
    passwordFocusNode.removeListener(passwordFocusIn);
    passwordFocusNode.addListener(passwordFocusOut);
  }

  void usernameFocusOut() {
    usernameFocusNode.addListener(usernameFocusIn);
    usernameFocusNode.removeListener(usernameFocusOut);

    usernameKey.currentState?.validate();
  }

  void passwordFocusOut() {
    passwordFocusNode.addListener(passwordFocusIn);
    passwordFocusNode.removeListener(passwordFocusOut);

    passwordKey.currentState?.validate();
  }
```

Note: I have no desire to prevent or undo the focusOut to force the user to respond to the validation failure. That's better left to the Submit

