A workaround for cases where your WidgetSpans contain text is to wrap them in a `SelectionArea` instead of a `SelectableText.Rich` widget.

This is not relevant for copying images, just text, but I'm sharing my code here in case someone needs similar functionality:

```dart
SelectionArea(
  child: Text.rich(
    TextSpan(
      children: tooltipSpans,
    )
)),
```

The tooltipSpans are WidgetSpans which will show a popup when tapped:
```dart
class TooltipSpan extends WidgetSpan {
  final InlineSpan inlineSpan;

  TooltipSpan({
    required Widget content,
    required this.inlineSpan,
    required SuperTooltipController controller,
  }) : super(
            child: GestureDetector(
          onTap: () async {
            await controller.showTooltip();
          },
          child: SuperTooltip(
            controller: controller,
            content: content,
            child: Text.rich(
              inlineSpan,
            ),
          ),
        ));
}
```

